<br>
Untill i was comfortable with the zone i parked my pet on the back side of 1 of the wiz spires faceing the spawn field. then I would pull bugs and bears to the pet. You wont see many griffs untill you get close to the gipsy camp. If things go wrong its just a short trip to the zone line and the guards will try to pick the wayward beast off of you.<br>
<br>
You can also post cam at the wooden bridge. I dont like this side of NK because there is a lack of spawn in this area. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujadexia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jadexia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(8/20/02 8:51:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Few spots</span><hr size=1> To be honest i did 12-14 rather easily in EC... Stick to the spot in front of the Hidden Inn (between the orc camps along the wall) Giant Spiders, Giant Scarabs and Woodland Lions make this spot sweet, all conned Dark blue and were easily solo able for me . Spawn times are such that  it is fast enough to keep it interesting, yet slow enough that you rarely get caught at half mana.. i used water pet as it's regen and resistance to poison works great against the spiders that will use a weak poison spell..<br>
